<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/142073-linda-c"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1182361969i/142073._UY100_CR24,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/142073-linda-c">Linda C.</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">My favorite translation of Orlando furioso is by Barbara Reynolds. It is by far the easiest to read and understand. <br/><br/>My biggest drawback with Waldman&apos;s<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">My favorite translation of Orlando furioso is by Barbara Reynolds. It is by far the easiest to read and understand. <br /><br />My biggest drawback with Waldman's version deals with the formatting by the publisher. It has tiny font, the text is compressed and it also is difficult to compare cantos and versions to a different translation by its layout.<br /><br />I also prefer the lyrical quality of verse over prose.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

